{"id": "EUVD-2019-8066", "enisaUuid": "08162b45-dd16-3427-87ec-7418171590e2", "description": "A flaw was found in HAProxy before 2.0.6. In legacy mode, messages featuring a transfer-encoding header missing the \"chunked\" value were not being correctly rejected. The impact was limited but if combined with the \"http-reuse always\" setting, it could be used to help construct an HTTP request smuggling attack against a vulnerable component employing a lenient parser that would ignore the content-length header as soon as it saw a transfer-encoding one (even if not entirely valid according to the specification).", "datePublished": "2019-10-23T13:07:01", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-05T01:47:14", "baseScore": 7.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:H/A:N", "references": ["https://www.suse.com/security/cve/CVE-2019-18277.html", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2020:2265", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2020:1936", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2020:1725", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2020:1287", "https://ubuntu.com/security/CVE-2019-18277", "https://linux.oracle.com/cve/CVE-2019-18277.html", "https://www.mail-archive.com/haproxy%40formilux.org/msg34926.html", "https://nathandavison.com/blog/haproxy-http-request-smuggling", "https://git.haproxy.org/?p=haproxy-2.0.git%3Ba=commit%3Bh=196a7df44d8129d1adc795da020b722614d6a581", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/4174-1/", "http://lists.opensuse.org/opensuse-security-announce/2019-12/msg00016.html", "http://lists.opensuse.org/opensuse-security-announce/2019-12/msg00019.html", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2022/05/msg00045.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2019-18277"], "assigner": "mitre", "epss": 0.83, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "340712df-797e-35be-9fc5-6ba040b4f690", "product": {"name": "n/a"}, "product_version": "n/a"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "13286ee9-ab4d-3a7b-902f-6a1d858af4ef", "vendor": {"name": "n/a"}}], "isExploited": false}